- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on investigating approaches and techniques related to the learning of source code changes to support the improvement of software projects.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses programming-by-example techniques used to differencing source code changes.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques to identify patterns in software repositories.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses the search approach used to identify relevant primary studies for the systematic review.
- cs.SD (Software Development) is another possible category as the paper focuses on the development process and strategies for identifying and suggesting source code changes.
